{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"criteria":[{"citation":{"description":"txn.py imports finalize_event from _seam.py; transition_core calls it at line 262, claim_core calls it at lines 354 and 374 for STATUS and EDIT events respectively.","kind":"file","line_end":39,"line_start":39,"path":"src/rebar/_commands/txn.py"},"criterion":"`transition_core` and `claim_core` in `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` sign their STATUS (and claim EDIT) events via the same signing seam CREATE/COMMENT use (`_apply_authorship` or an equivalent), so a transition/claim/close under a configured signing key produces `author_sig`.","kind":"codebase-verifiable","met":true},{"citation":{"description":"_AUTHORSHIP_GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES=(session_log,code_review,identity) at line 243; _apply_authorship raises CommandError for non-exempt unsignable events under require_authenticated (lines 317-325); finalize_event routes through this (line 346); txn.py calls finalize_event so the gate applies uniformly.","kind":"file","line_end":325,"line_start":239,"path":"src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py"},"criterion":"Under `identity.require_authenticated`, an unsignable transition of a non-exempt ticket is refused by the write-gate (parity with `append_event`), while gate-exempt types (session_log/code_review/identity) are unaffected.","kind":"codebase-verifiable","met":true},{"citation":{"description":"File present in test suite; tests cover: signed transition STATUS (line 82), signed claim STATUS+EDIT (lines 91-92), signed close STATUS (line 104), merge-gate exit 0 with enforcement on (line 124), and enforcement refusal with no identity/key (lines 135-137).","kind":"file","line_end":137,"line_start":1,"path":"tests/unit/test_identity_txn_signing_heldout.py"},"criterion":"A held-out regression test asserts: with a signing key configured, a transition/claim STATUS event has `author_sig` and `rebar verify-identity` reports it `verified`; without a key + enforcement on, the transition is refused. Proving command: `make test`.","kind":"codebase-verifiable","met":true},{"citation":{"description":"claim_core stages both STATUS and EDIT events then issues a single git commit ('ticket: CLAIM <id>') at line 382 under the held write lock, with index+file rollback in the except block (lines 383-391).","kind":"file","line_end":395,"line_start":380,"path":"src/rebar/_commands/txn.py"},"criterion":"No regression to txn atomicity/locking (claim writes STATUS+EDIT in one commit).","kind":"codebase-verifiable","met":true}],"findings":[],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_pass_v1","ticket_id":"0ba4-6a28-7a88-47b2","verdict":"PASS"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784250108004726001,"uuid":"08656d39-0f5d-4846-9ca3-ca6b894bc39e"}